Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.32,0:01:34.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen,\ngood evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.32,0:01:37.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The girl sleeping in the\nhouse of the poisoner...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.53,0:01:43.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...was saved thanks to the pure\nsouls of the young men.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.73,0:01:49.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, the next misfortune then silently\ncreeps up and suddenly appears before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.94,0:01:54.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, just like that single letter\nthat was delivered to an innocent soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.01,0:01:58.05,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 12:\NEncore
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.70,0:02:18.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.47,0:02:21.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Father, what did you\nsay just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.77,0:02:28.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your engagement to Albert...\NI've called it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.51,0:02:29.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.28,0:02:32.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's the meaning of this?\NWhat brought this on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.75,0:02:36.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've been hearing some unsavory rumors\nabout the Morcerf family.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.85,0:02:39.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But that doesn't mean you have to...\NI can't believe this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.12,0:02:41.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.06,0:02:46.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, you were never very enthusiastic\nover the engagement from the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.86,0:02:50.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't understand anything,\ndo you, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.30,0:02:55.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't treat my life like it was\none of your stocks or bonds!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.87,0:02:58.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here's a quick lesson\nfor you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.44,0:03:01.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There are only two kinds of people\nin this world, winners and losers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.14,0:03:07.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Eugenie, I'm only thinking\nof what's best for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.92,0:03:10.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Liar. You're thinking of\nwhat's best for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.83,0:03:22.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, Mondego,\nyou really blew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.73,0:03:26.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I plan to make it\nthrough this in one piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.37,0:03:33.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I must say, it's hard to believe you're\nthe Mondego I used to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.14,0:03:34.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've done well\nfor yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.94,0:03:38.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know\nabout that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.52,0:03:44.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A certain gentleman\nfilled me in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.55,0:03:46.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who?! Who was it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.33,0:03:55.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I can't tell you that...\NBut that's not important.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.50,0:03:58.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How much do\nyou want?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.20,0:04:03.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme everything\nyou've got!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.97,0:04:07.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you wanna keep me from talking,\Nstuff my mouth with gold!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.32,0:04:17.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's an honor to see you\nagain, Mademoiselle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.15,0:04:23.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Marquis Cavalcanti? Do you\nhave some business here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.39,0:04:25.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I have a meeting\nwith your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.16,0:04:28.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,More financial dealings?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.40,0:04:32.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was hoping that I might be\nof some assistance to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.94,0:04:40.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I want to take everything that causes\nyou sorrow and make them go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.54,0:04:44.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's no reason for\nyou to do that for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.82,0:04:50.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Does a man need a reason\nto be in love?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.46,0:04:55.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No! Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.73,0:04:57.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll scream!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.89,0:05:01.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're acquainted with the\NCount of Monte Cristo, I take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.60,0:05:08.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The gossip dealing with the Morcerf family\nwas apparently leaked by him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.74,0:05:10.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are you\ntalking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.81,0:05:15.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I must say, though, I find it unlikely that\nthe Count's information would be incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.81,0:05:18.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you telling\nme this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.18,0:05:25.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The thought of seeing sadness on the face\nof the woman I love is unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.49,0:05:30.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out. There's no reason\nfor you to be in love with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.53,0:05:39.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why would the Count of Monte\NCristo do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:51.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what she thinks about\Nthe engagement being called off?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.25,0:05:55.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you\njust ask the girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.32,0:06:01.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, this problem might be bigger\nthan just the two of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.26,0:06:04.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.19,0:06:07.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're serious about her,\naren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.03,0:06:14.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's true that you don't realize how\nimportant something is until you lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.14,0:06:20.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Goodness, this is amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.31,0:06:25.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is your daughter's big night, after all.\NMoney is no object.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.91,0:06:28.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My daughter is\na lucky girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.32,0:06:32.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She never would have been able to sell out\nthe opera house on her own merits.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.32,0:06:36.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This wouldn't have happened\Nwithout your gracious support.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.03,0:06:42.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, are you willing to go along with this?\NBreaking it off with Albert?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.37,0:06:48.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can hardly call it breaking it off.\NNothing had even started.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.87,0:06:51.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe, but you were engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.44,0:06:54.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is something that both\nour families decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.55,0:06:59.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you seem\nso hurt, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.08,0:07:04.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who is he? Who's this Count\nof Monte Cristo person?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.85,0:07:07.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did the Count have something\nto do with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.69,0:07:09.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's manipulating things\nbehind the scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.52,0:07:12.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like he was the source\nof all those bad rumors...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.26,0:07:14.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...about Uncle Fernand that\nmy father has been hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.86,0:07:16.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bad rumors?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.03,0:07:20.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, I don't care about\nall that political gossip,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.80,0:07:24.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but Albert hasn't been the same\never since he met that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.34,0:07:27.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I really miss the old days,\nyou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.04,0:07:32.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The three of us would run around the meadow,\nnot even noticing when the sun went down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.38,0:07:37.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When did it start?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.75,0:07:41.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When did we start being so awkward\naround each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.69,0:07:43.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and not even being able\nto hold hands anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.00,0:07:50.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When you were on your trip to Luna,\nwhat happened to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.87,0:07:54.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You two haven't been the same\nsince that trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.31,0:08:04.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, we haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.88,0:08:08.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What does Albert think\nabout all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.02,0:08:10.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't heard\nfrom him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.59,0:08:13.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Has he said anything\nto you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.72,0:08:16.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You two are\nbest friends, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.42,0:08:18.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Best friends, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.07,0:08:33.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Franz, is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.41,0:08:38.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I don't really understand\nhim these days, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.35,0:08:41.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen\nbetween you and Albert?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.12,0:08:44.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We got into\na fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.02,0:08:49.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert shouldn't associate\nwith the Count anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.23,0:08:55.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for\nlending an ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.73,0:08:58.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry I couldn't be more helpful. Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.80,0:09:00.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.04,0:09:02.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.31,0:09:08.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, whatever you might say about it,\Nit looks\nlike you really do care about Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.31,0:09:13.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, geez...\NIs it that obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.28,0:09:17.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No one can hide it when they're\npining away for someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.32,0:09:24.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the reason your piano performance\nthat night at Auteuil was so great...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.96,0:09:28.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...was because you were really\nplaying for Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.30,0:09:30.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.60,0:09:34.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The feelings you have for someone\nmanifest themselves in your art.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.60,0:09:35.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.89,0:10:01.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he wouldn't\nbe here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.47,0:10:07.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,After all,\nwe're still fighting...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.18,0:10:20.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he wouldn't\nbe here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.66,0:10:37.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's keeping her?\NIsn't Eugenie ready yet?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.43,0:10:39.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She is still\ngetting ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.60,0:10:43.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you're feeling well,\NMademoiselle?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.87,0:10:48.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine. This is the opera house performance\nthat I've always dreamed of.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.35,0:10:54.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's the strangest thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.52,0:10:57.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike the way it is\noutside the city walls,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.52,0:11:02.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...the muscat grapes here always bear fruit\nregardless of the season.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.03,0:11:05.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.70,0:11:13.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert, you should always\nlisten to your feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.60,0:11:19.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can't lie to yourself\nabout how you really feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.11,0:11:26.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Have you always been true\nto yourself, Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.68,0:11:30.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.45,0:11:32.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it truly is a paradise\nwhere you can find...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.25,0:11:34.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...whatever your heart desires\nif you work hard enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.32,0:11:41.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But if you lose your courage, you'll simply\nbe swept along on the currents.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.01,0:12:03.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to\nshow up, Albert?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.86,0:12:11.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you looking\nfor someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.69,0:12:12.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lucien!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.20,0:12:17.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it. Mother invited you,\ndidn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.80,0:12:19.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to her\nkind influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.83,0:12:23.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm dedicating my performance\ntonight to lovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.51,0:12:25.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you two\nenjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.41,0:12:30.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No. For tonight, you should play for yourself\nand for the person that you love.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.78,0:12:32.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Pianists are allowed\nto do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.55,0:12:36.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's easy for you\nto say...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.39,0:12:39.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.00,0:12:55.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert, my boy, I'm sorry, but the hall\nis already filled with invited guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.07,0:12:59.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have an invitation.\NEugenie gave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.88,0:13:04.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The past is the past.\NLet's pretend it never happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.01,0:13:10.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was invited by Eugenie!\NYou have no right to turn me away!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.25,0:13:15.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get that hot temper of yours\nfrom your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.46,0:13:17.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This has nothing to do with my father!\NI'm my own man!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.23,0:13:19.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to\nlet me pass!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.60,0:13:25.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And just what are you\ngoing to do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.43,0:13:28.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You have no power.\NYou have no money.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.50,0:13:30.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're nothing but\na spoiled brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.41,0:13:31.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.64,0:13:36.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe so, but I still...\NDamn it! Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.18,0:13:38.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's this commotion? This is supposed\nto be an auspicious occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.85,0:13:41.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you were invited, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.38,0:13:43.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, by Madame.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.75,0:13:51.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My wife seems to be feeling a little out of sorts.\NWould you mind keeping her company for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.19,0:13:56.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but I'm not in the mood today.\NExcuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.97,0:13:59.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out, Lucien!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.40,0:14:02.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I... have to get in there!\NListen!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.04,0:14:06.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Use your head, then!\NYou'll never get in through the front door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.34,0:14:09.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Crap...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.91,0:14:11.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't owe you any\nfavors or anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.75,0:14:15.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but I've been doing some things\nthat are hurting Eugenie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.42,0:14:19.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really sleeping\nwith Eugenie's mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.85,0:14:21.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's all part\nof my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.92,0:14:25.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never understand your whole life,\nand you don't have any need to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.13,0:14:28.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, be there for her and\nlisten to her performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.60,0:14:32.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You love Eugenie,\ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.34,0:14:35.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.66,0:17:12.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert?\NIs that you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.23,0:17:16.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're a little late,\ndon't you think?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.03,0:17:22.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was right here the whole time.\NI had a little trouble getting in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.17,0:17:24.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean my father,\ndo you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.47,0:17:29.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right, I heard\nyou play just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.91,0:17:31.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was really great.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.15,0:17:36.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You were radiant out there.\NMy heart was pounding!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.12,0:17:43.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot. If I'd known you were here,\NI would've been able to play even better.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.49,0:17:45.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I would've been playing\nfor you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.93,0:17:48.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Eugenie...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.98,0:18:05.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I know I'm not\nyour fiancée anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.51,0:18:08.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't matter.\NI don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.99,0:18:13.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.16,0:18:15.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.06,0:18:17.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You like these,\ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.86,0:18:22.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, sure, but you're supposed\nto bring a bouquet of flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.90,0:18:25.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. I guess flowers\nwould've been better...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.64,0:18:32.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a fool. You haven't\Nchanged one bit since we were kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.41,0:18:37.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Out in the meadow,\NI wanted you to pick flowers for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.98,0:18:42.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but you would always bring\nme berries instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.88,0:18:45.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They were delicious, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.67,0:19:00.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mademoiselle Eugenie!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.87,0:19:03.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It won't do to keep\nyour audience waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.91,0:19:04.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.74,0:19:06.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.51,0:19:12.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to one more song.\NI'll be playing it just for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.13,0:19:33.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like you've\nbeen shut out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.30,0:19:36.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be so sure\nabout that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.85,0:19:53.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen! Let's have a warm\Nround of applause for Mademoiselle Eugenie!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.39,0:19:59.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?!\NThis is my performance!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.99,0:20:03.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, one that I arranged.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.77,0:20:06.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.37,0:20:08.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know\nwhen to quit!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.27,0:20:14.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My daughter has set out on the road to\na bright future! Don't ruin it for her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.31,0:20:16.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have any\nright to be here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.98,0:20:21.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All the seats for tonight's performance\nwere bought out by Marquis Cavalcanti!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.85,0:20:23.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've lost,\nso go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.40,0:20:41.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.97,0:20:46.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why, whatever is the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.38,0:20:50.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're not looking\nwell at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.15,0:20:56.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.68,0:20:57.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.29,0:21:00.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm... so frustrated...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.76,0:21:06.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At how weak\nand pathetic I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.20,0:21:14.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count of Monte Cristo!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.20,0:21:17.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You are under suspicion\nof criminal activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.74,0:21:21.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I will have to ask you to come with me\nto the station as the prime suspect...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.18,0:21:22.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...in the poisoning death\nof Valois!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.91,0:21:24.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Monsieur Villefort...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.79,0:23:12.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Villefort's investigation\nis relentless.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.15,0:23:14.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.32,0:23:17.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When I go to visit the Count, I sit and\nspeak with Haidee for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.76,0:23:20.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Gankutsuou,\NThe Count of Monte Cristo act 13:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.17,0:23:21.17,count fo,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 13:\NHaidee
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.73,0:23:21.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,..."Haidee."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.86,0:23:24.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bide your time,\nand hold out hope!
